Brazil ' 97 foreign direct investment seen $ 15 bln . Foreign direct investment in Brazil is likely to reach $ 15 billion in 1997 , up from $ 9 . 889 billion last year , a Central Bank official said . Altamir Lopes , chief of the Central Bank ' s economic department , also told reporters foreign direct investment totalled $ 270 million in the first 13 days of June . Earlier the Central Bank said foreign direct investment totalled $ 6 . 3 billion from January to May . ( ( - - Fatima Cristina , Sao Paulo newsroom 5511 2485412 ) ) 
